The infringing page contains text from my original article.

The only text on the infringing page that is not taken from the original article is "HP has recently reveal its latest HP m6-1045dx a 15.6-inch screen size laptop that features" and "The HP m6-1045dx is priced $729.99".

Everything else is taken from the original article.

"...Intel’s 3rd Generation Core i5-3210M “Ivy Bridge” dual-core processor." is taken from the 2nd paragraph of the original article. 

"...750GB hard drive and 8GB of RAM, up to 640GB and 6GB on the 1035dx." is taken from the 3rd paragraph of he original.

The whole paragraph after "HP m6-1045dx Specifications" subtitle on the infringing page is copied from the original article (the last paragraph, under "HP m6-1045dx Specifications" subtitle).

Images are not a part of this DMCA complaint.
